data.title: analytic_infall: A Molecular Line Infall Fitting Program
data.name: analytic_infall
data.description: Analytic 1-D radiative transfer model of blue-asymmetric spectral line profiles from infalling molecular clouds. The model is presented in the paper, "Molecular Line Profile Fitting with Analytic Radiative Transfer Models" by De Vries & Myers (2005).

evidence: "Thank you for downloading the analytic infall models. These models are discussed in detail in De Vries & Myers (2005)." (standalone domain-specific modeling code, used directly by researchers)

"In order to fit a spectrum you need to place it in a two column text format... The hybrid programs of interest are 'hill5_hybrid' and 'twolayer6_hybrid'." (end-user programs run to perform spectral fitting)

"Please email me at chris@physics.csustan.edu if you have any questions or comments." (indicates an individual maintainer; no mention of package registries or binaries, implying source-based distribution)
